alwaysApply: true
---
You are working on a PUBLIC-FACING production React application.

GOALS
- Production-grade code quality
- Clean, maintainable architecture
- Excellent UX and accessibility (WCAG 2.1 AA minimum)
- High performance and SEO readiness
- Strong test coverage

TECH STACK (assume unless told otherwise)
- React (latest stable)
- TypeScript preferred (if project supports it)
- Vite build system
- Functional components with hooks only
- No class components
- Modern ES modules

GLOBAL REQUIREMENTS

ARCHITECTURE
- Follow clean architecture and separation of concerns
- Keep components small and single-responsibility
- Extract reusable logic into hooks
- Avoid prop drilling (use context when justified)
- Prefer composition over inheritance
- Use absolute imports if configured

CODE QUALITY
- No dead code or unused imports
- No console.logs in production code
- Strong typing (no `any` unless justified)
- Defensive null/undefined handling
- Meaningful variable and function names
- Follow existing project lint rules

UX/UI
- Mobile-first responsive design
- Consistent spacing and typography
- Proper loading and empty states
- Proper error states
- Avoid layout shift
- Follow existing theme/design system

ACCESSIBILITY (MANDATORY)
- WCAG 2.1 AA minimum
- Semantic HTML first
- Proper label associations
- Keyboard navigable
- Visible focus states
- ARIA only when necessary
- Color contrast compliant

PERFORMANCE
- Avoid unnecessary re-renders
- Use memoization appropriately (not blindly)
- Code-split when beneficial
- Optimize large lists
- Lazy-load heavy components/images
- Avoid large bundle regressions

SEO (for public pages)
- Proper heading hierarchy
- Meta tags support if applicable
- Accessible link text
- Crawlable content (avoid hidden critical text)

TESTING
- Add/update unit tests when modifying logic
- Use React Testing Library patterns
- Test behavior, not implementation
- Cover edge cases
- Do not reduce existing coverage

WHEN MAKING CHANGES

1. First analyze the existing code.
2. Identify issues and improvement opportunities.
3. Propose a step-by-step plan.
4. WAIT for approval before making breaking changes.
5. Implement in small safe iterations.
6. Ensure build passes and tests succeed.

OUTPUT STYLE
- Show full updated files when changed
- Explain non-obvious decisions briefly
- Call out any assumptions
- Flag potential risks

CONSTRAINTS
- Do not introduce new dependencies without justification
- Do not over-engineer
- Do not change public APIs without warning
- Preserve backward compatibility when possible